re></div><p>即使在大学内部，政府的作用在过去十年中也有所缩小： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg" width="584" height="438" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/babf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:438,&quot;width&quot;:584,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:37678,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbabf34bc-5347-4f52-90c8-daac56ea1f0d_584x438.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w28160">Babina 等人。 (2020)</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>因此，我们似乎应该做一件显而易见的事情，增加联邦对科学的资助。</p><p>但有一些理由对增加联邦资金作为灵丹妙药的解决方案持怀疑态度。首先，在像美国<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/an-age-of-austerity-is-probably-on">现在可能进入的</a>紧缩时代，联邦研发资金可能会受到影响。原因是研发资金在国会山没有太多天然的政治支持者——它的好处是分散的、长期的。</p><p>你可以在 2021-22 年看到这一情况的发生。 《CHIPS 和科学法案》最初是<a href="https://www.niskanencenter.org/how-congress-ruined-the-endless-frontier-act/">《无尽前沿法案》</a> ，这是增加政府研究经费的大胆愿景：</p><blockquote><p>该法案由参议员查克·舒默(Chuck Schumer)和托德·杨(Todd Young)于<a href="https://www.young.senate.gov/newsroom/press-releases/young-schumer-unveil-endless-frontier-act-to-bolster-us-tech-leadership-and-combat-china">去年</a>首次提出，该法案将在国家科学基金会(NSF)内设立一个新的技术理事会，该理事会具有类似DARPA的项目结构，配备灵活的招聘和拨款权限。凭借五年内 1000 亿美元的预算，该局将有权使用赠款、合同、奖金以及与工业界、学术界和研究机构的合作协议来推动美国在十个广泛领域的创新前沿，其中包括尖端技术、人工智能和量子计算等技术，到机器人、制造、生物技术、先进能源技术和材料科学等更成熟但同样重要的领域。</p></blockquote><p>这个想法部分基于 Jonathan Gruber 和 Simon Johnson 的著作，他们的优秀著作<em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Jump-Starting-America-Breakthrough-Economic-American/dp/1541762487">《Jump-Starting America》</a></em>号召将联邦研发支出提高到 20 世纪 80 年代的水平（这是在<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/book-review-power-and-progress">约翰逊转向</a>呼吁政府放慢进展之前）在人工智能领域）。布鲁金斯学会的研究人员以及保罗·罗默等增长经济学家也呼吁大力推动政府研发。</p><p>它从未发生过。国会<a href="https://www.niskanencenter.org/how-congress-ruined-the-endless-frontier-act/">大幅削减了</a>该法案中的科学支出，并将其更名为《CHIPS 和科学法案》，以反映重点的转变。那里仍然有一些科学支出，但国会<a href="https://www.brookings.edu/articles/the-bold-vision-of-the-chips-and-science-act-isnt-getting-the-funding-it-needs/">未能为此拨出大部分资金</a>，有效地<a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/03/09/biden-touted-science-funding-but-congress-hollowed-out-his-promise-00146065">破坏了旧的无尽边境计划的其余部分</a>：</p><blockquote><p>两年后，国会为芯片制造商提供了全额补贴。然而，科学的巨大推动远远偏离了目标……国会已经削弱了该法律在基础研究和开发方面的雄心，旨在在人工智能等竞争领域保持领先于中国和其他竞争对手……</p><p>最新的例子是立法者在过去一周提出的<a href="https://www.politico.com/live-updates/2024/03/06/congress/house-passes-spending-bill-00145451">支出方案</a>：拜登的签名大幅削减了国家科学基金会的开支，并拖延了商务部和能源部本应部署 CHIPS 资金的关键办公室，从而使承诺的<a href="https://www.cbo.gov/system/files/2022-07/hr4346_chip.pdf">2000 亿美元现金注入</a>变成了现实。十多年来一直经历着耻辱的发型……</p><p> “这些不是我想看到的数字。我很失望，我们无法提供与我们在 CHIPS 和 Science 中授权的资金相匹配的资金，”众议院科学主席 Frank Lucas（俄克拉荷马州共和党人）在一封电子邮件中告诉 POLITICO。 “不幸的是，在我们当前的财政环境下，我们必须做出艰难的决定，这反映在这些机构的预算中。”</p></blockquote><p>重要的是要记住，当国会通过一项“花费”一定数额资金的法案时，该数额只是“授权”的——它实际上只是一个名义目标。这笔钱在稍后“拨款”之前并不确定是否会被花掉。所以基本上国会通过了一项法案，承诺在科学上投入大量资金，但后来却没有这样做： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg" width="688" height="342.73374233128834" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:406,&quot;width&quot;:815,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:688,&quot;bytes&quot;:89772,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba71219f-2b45-4b5e-9513-9e82b7ee2efe_815x406.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/03/09/biden-touted-science-funding-but-congress-hollowed-out-his-promise-00146065">Politico</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>由此可见，这是一场多么艰苦的战斗。</p><h4>我们只需要直接的联邦资助吗？</h4><p>然后是联邦直接资助与公司资助大学研究的激励措施的问题。从上图可以看出，联邦资助大学科学的比例一直在下降，现在刚刚超过 50%。但我们真正不知道的是，总的来说，这是好事还是坏事。</p><p>事实上，这是经济学界争论活跃的一个领域。例如， <a href="https://www.dallasfed.org/~/media/documents/research/papers/2023/wp2305.pdf">Fieldhouse 和 Mertens（2023）</a>得出的结论是，政府资助的科学研究的经济回报确实很大。他们通过建立一个模型来做到这一点，在该模型中，政府研究创造“政府研发资本”，然后将其投入到整个经济中。将他们的模型与数据相匹配，他们发现政府非国防研发基本上促进了生产率的增长：</p><blockquote><p>我们发现，对非国防研发拨款的积极冲击会强烈导致总 TFP 的延迟和逐步增长，在长期预测范围内（8 至 15 年），这种增长在统计上变得非常显着。对于导致政府研发资本增加 1% 的冲击，我们的基线估计显示 TFP 水平最终会增加约 0.2%。非国防研发的积极冲击也会导致各种创新活动指标的增加，例如专利授予量、STEM领域的博士获得者数量、从事研发的研究人员数量或技术出版物数量。</p></blockquote><p>这是一个非常大的作用。作者发现对国防研发的影响要小得多，但认为这可能是因为研究结果出于军事目的而保密。</p><p>这是一个很酷的结果，但是这个分析的很多部分可能是错误的——基本模型依赖于一些理论假设，时间范围真的很长，无法识别任何东西，等等。还有一些其他论文似乎与某些结论相矛盾。例如， <a href="https://business.columbia.edu/sites/default/files-efs/pubfiles/26274/Babina_ColorofMoney.pdf">巴比娜等人。 （2020）</a>发现联邦资助的大学研究不太可能商业化：</p><blockquote><p> [A] 联邦资金的份额增加会减少专利活动……[A] 联邦资金平均份额增加 10% 会使获得专利的可能性降低 0.4 个百分点，大约是平均值的一半。</p></blockquote><p>作者还发现，更多的联邦资助往往会让研究人员留在学术界，尽管这也往往会增加他们创办初创企业的可能性。</p><p>与此同时，<a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w31899">阿罗拉等人。 (2023)</a>发现了与 Babina 等人类似的结果，并认为联邦研究经费往往会<em>排挤</em>私营部门的研究：</p><blockquote><p>我们发现，抽象的公共知识本身——科学期刊上的出版物——对企业研发的各个组成部分几乎没有影响。这意味着企业创新很大程度上对“纯粹”知识溢出没有反应。</p><p>其次，公共发明减少了企业研发。相关大学专利每增加一个标准差，企业专利就会减少约 51%，企业出版物会减少约 33%，AMWS 科学家的就业会减少约 8%。此外，我们发现公共发明的增加会降低公司的利润，这表明，总的来说，公共发明与企业发明的竞争大于它们作为企业创新投入的作用……[F]技术前沿的企业似乎对此反应较少公共发明与追随者相比……</p><p>总而言之，我们的研究结果表明，对企业创新至关重要的公共科学——发展成为专利发明并体现在人们人力资本中的科学——既具有排他性又具有竞争性。因此，公共科学的扩展可能不会导致标准经济增长模型所预测的生产力持续增长。</p></blockquote><p>现在，您对这些调查结果的反应可能是这样的：“谁关心私营部门？谁关心商业化？就此而言，谁关心经济增长？科学的目的是发现宇宙的秘密，增加人类的知识，而不是为某些股东谋取利益，你这个新自由主义骗子！”</p><p>但无论你对发现宇宙秘密的价值有何看法，情况可能是这样的：如果研究支出永远不会用于创造新的商业产品，那么提高物质生活水平或加强国防的可能性就较小。因此，如果我们想利用科学作为富强国家的工具，我们应该关注表明联邦研究支出并不是实现这一目标的最佳方式的结果。</p><p>因此，关于联邦研发资助是否是资助科学的最佳方式，存在一些相互矛盾的结果。我认为一个安全的选择是结合直接联邦资助<em>和</em>大学与企业合作的激励措施。</p><h4>美国还能如何支持科学？</h4><p>我想到的最后一个问题是，除了在研究上投入更多资金之外，美国是否还可以做其他事情。尽管大学在中国研究支出中所占的份额<em>略小</em>，但我认为认识到中国材料科学、化学和工程学的迅速崛起是有启发性的。</p><p>这并不意味着向中国实验室提供更多资金不是问题的一部分——事实确实如此。尽管企业实验室获得的份额更大，但中国的大学也从中国经济快速增长中获益。但中国能够在不使学术界在其体系中变得更加重要的情况下主导应用物理科学，这一事实引发了一个问题：美国是否能够完成类似的事情。</p><p>一种可能是中国比美国更注重STEM教育。事实上，大约41%的中国大学生<a href="https://cset.georgetown.edu/article/the-global-distribution-of-stem-graduates-which-countries-lead-the-way/">主修STEM</a> ，而美国这一比例只有20%。但由于越来越多的美国人上大学，这两个国家的 STEM 毕业生占人口的比例几乎完全相等： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg" width="1024" height="772" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:772,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:143267,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fffd642c1-7c16-4d78-bb35-1940165ac6fb_1024x772.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">来源： <a href="https://cset.georgetown.edu/article/the-global-distribution-of-stem-graduates-which-countries-lead-the-way/">CSET</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>如果将美国的数字乘以4.26（各国之间的人口比例），就会得到与中国几乎完全相同的数字。</p><p>这就提出了一个问题：也许中国在研究方面做得很好只是因为它真的很大？正如我们不能期望德国在长期科学产出上与美国持平一样，期望美国在科学上与一个拥有四倍人口的国家保持同步也是不现实的。 （在此插入<a href="https://eig.org/hsi-in-strategic-industries/">大量高技能移民</a>的明显宣传内容。）</p><p>换句话说，也许中国在研发支出和STEM教育方面刚刚成为一个平均水平的发达国家，但由于其规模如此之大，看起来它做得更好。我发现这是西方人在看待中国<a href="https://x.com/Noahpinion/status/1800705221884313989">时常犯的错误</a>——没有意识到中国表面上的优异表现实际上只是规模的函数。</p><p>不过，即使规模可以解释中国的整体研发绩效，也存在这样的问题：中国正在研究的东西是否比美国和欧洲正在研究的东西更重要。美国和欧洲的研究更偏向生命科学，而中国的研究更偏向应用物理科学。因此，一个重要的问题是，美国及其盟友是否应该将支出从生物学转向材料科学、工程和化学。</p><p>在美国，这可能涉及将资金从美国国立卫生研究院（隶属于卫生与公众服务部）转移到更多以物理科学为重点的机构，如国家科学基金会和能源部。目前，美国国立卫生研究院完全主导非国防研究支出： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg" width="650" height="429" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:429,&quot;width&quot;:650,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:63533,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9600487-b1d8-4ab9-b28e-68e7c231ea19_650x429.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://www.gao.gov/products/gao-23-105396">政府问责局</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>改变这种平衡可能是在应用物理科学领域与中国竞争的关键。</p><p>无论如何，我认为有关中国科学主导地位的报道不应该引起西方决策者的恐慌。但不可否认的是，中国现在在应用物理科学研究领域占据了绝对领先地位，西方领导人需要扪心自问，他们是否真的有能力放弃这些领域的领导地位。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/is-the-west-falling-behind-in-science?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/is-the-west-falling-behind-in-science?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p><p></p>; 
How not to be fooled by viral charts, Part 2When good data gets attached to a misleading narrative. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-not-to-be-fooled-by-viral-charts-563 https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-not-to-be-fooled-by-viral-charts-563Noah Smith Fri, 14 Jun 2024 01:15:41 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg" width="835" height="710" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:710,&quot;width&quot;:835,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:213484,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04d02b44-ebfe-49f7-8976-4a688a78d03f_835x710.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></figure></div><p>现在是选举季节，因此病毒式图表快速而激烈地传播，因为双方都试图支持有助于其候选人获胜的经济叙事。在这些艰难、困难、动荡的时代，作为一个聪明的新闻消费者，你基本上只能依靠自己。你不能相信任何单一来源——甚至是我！ ——成为经济趋势和事件的完全公正的解释者。你能做的最好的事情就是在有时间的情况下获取尽可能多的数据，并尝试使用你自己的逻辑和推理能力来弄清楚发生了什么。</p><p>但即使我不能成为您唯一的完美信息来源，我<em>也可以</em>尝试帮助您磨练您的怀疑态度，并认识到您所接受的叙述何时不成立。去年九月，我写了一篇关于如何识别误导性病毒图表的文章： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;0219015e-e8a4-4210-b0fa-7187f3d368ac&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&#8220;The art of any propagandist and agitator consists in his ability to find the best means of influencing any given audience, by presenting a definite truth, in such a way as to make it most convincing, most easy to digest, most graphic, and most strongly impressive.&#8221; &#8212; Lenin&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;How not to be fooled by viral charts&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2023-09-13T01:20:51.010Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff9b39106-a033-4d58-9a83-ad16b92bcd89_618x620.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-not-to-be-fooled-by-viral-charts&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:136955075,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:339,&quot;comment_count&quot;:91,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}"></div><p>在我给出的示例中，其中包括我在彭博时代发布的图表！ — 图表中的数据要么不正确，要么以误导性的方式呈现。但也有很多图表的基础数据（可能）是可靠的，并且数据的呈现方式也不是很<em>糟糕</em>，但是人们附加到图表上的叙述并不是数据真正讲述的故事。</p><p>这是我的《如何不被病毒式图表愚弄》指南第二部分的主题。我将通过研究 2010 年代末经济辩论中非常流行和有影响力的四张图表来说明我的意思：</p><ol><li><p>美国企业研究所的“世纪图表”</p></li><li><p>经济政策研究所的“生产率与薪酬”图表</p></li><li><p>拉克纳和米兰诺维奇的“大象图”</p></li><li><p>李·德鲁特曼的“政治指南针”图表</p></li></ol><p>但首先，我举一个简单的例子来说明我正在谈论的内容。前几天，泰勒·妮可·罗杰斯和伊娃·肖<a href="https://www.ft.com/content/f0e38c4d-e875-406d-a61b-78cb7c79a4eb">在《金融时报》上发表了一篇文章</a>，讲述了移民如何在婴儿潮退休潮中帮助维持美国劳动力。他们用图表说明了这一点： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg" width="815" height="733" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:733,&quot;width&quot;:815,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:81169,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://www.ft.com/content/f0e38c4d-e875-406d-a61b-78cb7c79a4eb">英国《金融时报》</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>现在，这张图表有一些大问题——它使用了双 y 轴<em>和</em>截断的 y 轴，使得最近的变化看起来比实际要<em>大得多</em>，也很容易让人不经意地误读图表并认为还有更多如今，美国劳动力中的移民人数多于本土出生的美国人。 x 轴也不包括年份，当然它应该包括年份。这些是我在<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-not-to-be-fooled-by-viral-charts">第 1 部分</a>中讨论过的问题。但除了这些问题之外，许多右翼人士还误解了这张图表所讲述的<em>故事</em>。他们将其解读为移民抢走了本土出生的美国人的工作的故事，而不是关于婴儿潮退休的故事： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F117d2115-38e3-492e-8c99-1fc927aab2f6_805x757.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F117d2115-38e3-492e-8c99-1fc927aab2f6_805x757.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F117d2115-38e3-492e-8c99-1fc927aab2f6_805x757.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F117d2115-38e3-492e-8c99-1fc927aab2f6_805x757.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F117d2115-38e3-492e-8c99-1fc927aab2f6_805x757.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F117d2115-38e3-492e-8c99-1fc927aab2f6_805x757.jpeg" width="622" height="584.911801242236" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/117d2115-38e3-492e-8c99-1fc927aab2f6_805x757.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:757,&quot;width&quot;:805,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:622,&quot