:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1f3a9f5a-fb0c-4edf-8be3-274ac741e9b3_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1f3a9f5a-fb0c-4edf-8be3-274ac741e9b3_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1f3a9f5a-fb0c-4edf-8be3-274ac741e9b3_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1f3a9f5a-fb0c-4edf-8be3-274ac741e9b3_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>换句话说，一张关于婴儿潮退休的图表被误解为一张关于移民就业的图表——在这种情况下，是故意的，并且出于政治原因。数据不错，但叙述是错误的。</p><p>不管怎样，让我们​​来看看 2010 年代的四个著名例子。</p><h4>示例 1：“世纪图表”</h4><p> 1992 年至 2020 年间，美国的通货膨胀率总体较低且稳定。但较低的总体通货膨胀率掩盖了个别商品和服务价格的显着变化——有些东西变得更贵，而另一些东西则便宜得多。在一张通常被称为“<a href="https://www.aei.org/carpe-diem/chart-of-the-day-century-price-changes-1997-to-2017/">世纪图表”的</a>图表中，马克·佩里和美国企业研究所的其他一些人展示了其中一些不同的价格变化。医疗保健、教育和儿童保育都变得更加昂贵，而汽车、服装、家具、电子产品、手机服务和软件都变得更便宜。住房和食物介于两者之间。 Perry（现已退休）最近制作了<a href="https://x.com/Mark_J_Perry/status/1747995005518516419">图表的更新版本</a>，稍微移动了起点和终点，但图表看起来基本相同，所以我将使用这个新版本： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg" width="706" height="615.7888888888889" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:785,&quot;width&quot;:900,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:706,&quot;bytes&quot;:176711,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe3373518-4a44-4e83-b210-e0f092dd391e_900x785.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://x.com/Mark_J_Perry/status/1747995005518516419">马克·佩里</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这里的基础数据没有问题——它来自劳工统计局。美国劳工统计局并不总是把所有事情都做到完美无缺——没有人做到这一点——但他们竭尽全力，而且他们有很多聪明的人不知疲倦地工作，以使这些数据尽可能准确。</p><p>我对该图表呈现数据的方式确实有两个小问题。首先，大学学费数字是<em>标题</em>数字，不包括<em>经济援助</em>。学生实际支付的大学学费<a href="https://libertystreeteconomics.newyorkfed.org/2019/06/the-cost-of-college-continues-to-climb/">增长速度比官方标价慢得多</a>，并且<a href="https://www.brookings.edu/articles/college-prices-arent-skyrocketing-but-theyre-still-too-high-for-some/">在2006年之后根本没有增长</a>。其次，佩里选择将住房和食品标记为红色，因为它们的上涨速度略快于总体通货膨胀率，这一点有点可疑——两者的增长速度都比工资慢，因此在这段时间内它们变得<em>更加负担得起</em>，而不是更少。 。</p><p>但这些都是小问题。总体而言，这是一张具有良好数据的良好图表，它说明了近几十年来美国经济的一个清晰而重要的事实：<strong>实物商品普遍变得更便宜，而服务普遍变得更昂贵</strong>。</p><p>然而， <a href="https://x.com/search?q=%22chart%20of%20the%20century%22%20government&amp;src=typed_query&amp;f=top">许多人看到这张图表</a>后，相信它揭示了服务价格上涨的<em>根本原因</em>。他们认为这完全取决于政府的参与和监管： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2e2eac1a-49b6-4783-ba85-c3f42c8dacc3_914x386.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2e2eac1a-49b6-4783-ba85-c3f42c8dacc3_914x386.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2e2eac1a-49b6-4783-ba85-c3f42c8dacc3_914x386.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2e2eac1a-49b6-4783-ba85-c3f42c8dacc3_914x386.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2e2eac1a-49b6-4783-ba85-c3f42c8dacc3_914x386.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2e2eac1a-49b6-4783-ba85-c3f42c8dacc3_914x386.jpeg" width="612" height="258.4595185995624" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2e2eac1a-49b6-4783-ba85-c3f42c8dacc3_914x386.jpeg&